        <num>CC 1591</num>
        <heading>1591.  Accretion of particular and general legacies</heading>
        <content>
          <p>Art. 1591.  Accretion of particular and general legacies
When a particular or a general legacy lapses, accretion takes place in favor of the successor who, under the testament, would have received the thing if the legacy had not been made.</p>
        </content>
